column5: Bray forced me out even with the flu.
Bite slowed abit but I got two more  T shirt weather down here now!!!
big sucky baby when you're sick eh  you ever night fish that spot this time of year? I'm guessing it would be crazy.
Lot's of action anyway maybe some bigger ones will come!  Thanks for sharing,  MTBF

Yeah it wasnt fun upchucking a few times lol but i managed to hold down some gatoraide  Many times I fish that spot at night and you are correct! I put my ice shack right there in the winter too and at night you can get triple digits
Thank mike! Its all about eaters now. Biguns will be here anytime now and you wont catch eaters anymore, theyll all be 25-32"s
Show us some pix of those big girls.  Your area is awesome - I'd love to be there right now!  My mind is planning a trip there next season already!
Good times, tight lines and family fun....Gotta love it!!!
Show us some pix of those big girls.  Your area is awesome - I'd love to be there right now!  My mind is planning a trip there next season already! OK, but these are still swimming about............
Must be nice!  All I would catch at my local river is a shopping cart
i spy with my little eye something called a sauger...and a big one at that  get an IV drip and fish that flu away lol
You are very fortunate to be so close to an amazing fishery.  You wouldn't be able to get me off the water if I had those results in my area.
i spy with my little eye something called a sauger...and a big one at that  get an IV drip and fish that flu away lol I don't see a Sauger
